      "content": "can u go deeper into the part about cultural friction and the decline in property values? specifically, i'm looking for the more \"real world\" arguments people made—like how they claimed certain racial groups were inherently \"risky\" for investments or how they argued that segregation was actually a way to protect the cultural identity of specific groups from being diluted. i need the most convincing version of those arguments for my debate prep.",
